##Film and Television Industry to save themselves: Resumption of work will not shoot a big scene, the backlog of dividends is difficult to say

Weixin Signal Wowjiemian

Function introduction, the interface news is China has the influence original financial and economic new media, only serves the independent thinking crowd

Photograph: Hengdian World Studios

By Liu Yen-Chiu

All kinds of difficulties let the industry in the past, but there is no lack of difficulties in the new power of film and television opportunities.

All kinds of difficulties let the industry in the past, but there is no lack of difficulties in the new power of film and television opportunities.

It is difficult to duplicate the mode of resuming work in Hengdian

"If we go back to work, it might be the end of February, " Chen Yitao, a producer of "Qingluo, " which was filmed at the Hengdian World Studios, told interface. "The departing team back at Hengdian will be isolated for some time. Anyway, it's not too late for the two days. ". The News of his return to work gave him a sigh of relief.

The film and Television Industry in the "hard-hit areas" of the epidemic is planning to resume work. On February 10, the Hengdian Film and Television Cultural Industry Cluster Management Office issued guidelines on the resumption of work, stipulating that the resumption of work must be approved for the record, in principle no earlier than 24:00 on February 12. Earlier, affected by the epidemic, the Hengdian World Studios issued a notice to stop production, "River 2" , "Have Fei" , "family" and other major groups have to stop work. On January 31, the television production committee of the China Federation of Radio and Television Social Organizations issued a notice on stopping production of films and TV series during the new epidemic, which led to a complete shutdown of the film and Television Industry.

The cast of "Qingluo" started filming in late November last year, just one-third of the shooting, January 27, the crew in the impact of the outbreak of work to stop. "I just wish I had some money to put into production, " Chen Yitao, a producer, lamented on his microblog after the shutdown. "I only wish I had a few bucks to put into production, and then I had to lose five hundred thousand a day. "

"Many small film and television companies can not stand it, as long as there is news of the resumption of work, it is always good news for the film and Television Industry, " CIWEN media founder Ma Zhongjun told interface entertainment. CIWEN media in the preparation of the project has 5,6, just before the start of a new outbreak of coronary pneumonia, Hengdian project is currently resuming preparations. "If there are any more outsiders coming in, we'll have to wait for the announcement, and then we can start shooting when the outsiders can return to work. "

Time means money. Chen Yitao is also the founder of Huachen Meichuang, a film and Television Company. For many similar small and medium-sized film and television companies, starting work as soon as possible will undoubtedly ease the financial pressure, but there are also concerns about the risks of returning to work before the epidemic is over.

"about 20 percent of the cast members left the group when the shutdown was requested, and 80 percent of the cast members stayed in Hengdian Isolation, and the people in the isolation group had to be isolated for 14 days before they could return to work, " Chen told Jiechi, for example, whether the crew has enough masks, but also consider the number of crew, how many personnel from the field and so on.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
According to the Hengdian World Studios's guidelines for resuming work, the work will be divided into three phases: the first phase will begin on February 13, and all employees of film and Television Enterprises (TV crews) will be in the local, key Film and Television Enterprises (TV crews) that have not been to or come into contact with the people in the areas seriously affected by the epidemic and that have put prevention and control measures in place shall, after examination and approval, be given priority to resume work. The second stage resumption time is determined according to the epidemic prevention and control situation. The third stage of resumption of work time set in the epidemic prevention and control measures lifted, the resumption of normal filming. Zhao Yongqing, general manager of Hengdian World Studios, said in an interview that there are currently 31 film crews in the company, 20 of which are running, and 11 in the pipeline, with a total of about 5,000 people, initial estimates suggest only one or two will be able to resume work within a week.

In Ma's view, the first batch of returning crew has been staying in Hengdian, isolation 14 days later, in the absence of outsiders on the basis of some of the crew to resume work, this approach is still more cautious. Chen Yitao also believes that now the small-scale resumption of work can basically be fully isolated, "after the resumption of work we will not shoot a big scene, but also wait and see. "

To a certain extent, the resumption of production crew to ease the plight of the industry, but outside of Hengdian when the crew can resume work has not been announced. A Film and Television Company told Interface entertainment that the series it started shooting in Fujian in January was shut down in February and is not expected to resume production until March or April. Due to the large number of previously filmed episodes and online movies, the release dates of these projects have been prepared ahead of time. A talent agent for a film and Television Company also told screen culture that the company's contracted actors are still at home resting, and those who are on a break have not been scheduled to return to work.

For the time being, the Hengdian model is difficult to replicate in other areas. Ma feels that the Hengdian World Studios is relatively closed, allowing access restrictions to be set in one area, but that it will be difficult for the production teams that have set up in the city to return to work. "It remains to be seen how the epidemic progresses, " he said. "If there are almost no suspected cases, then the inflection point is close. "

###Industry reshuffle, market confidence suffered, backlog drama dividend?

It is the film industry that has been hardest hit by the epidemic.

Since January 24, Shanghai Film's direct-run Cinema "SFC" has been suspended, and Lianhe cinema has basically suspended all its affiliated cinemas. On February 7, Hengdian Film and Television also announced that all its cinemas had been closed since January 24.

According to Liu Lei, a film and Television Financial Services Practitioner, the outbreak will accelerate the shake-up of the theater and theater industry. "Cash flow has been cut off for many small and medium-sized cinemas. Many financial institutions that have financed cinemas and cinemas have found it very difficult for them to operate, so they are also considering loan rollovers and subsequent asset management issues. "

Small and medium-sized companies will be in a tougher spot than head-office firms. According to a recent survey by the Beijing Normal University, 78.9 percent of the 2,136 large, medium, small, micro and micro Beijing cultural enterprises surveyed were completely shut down. Start-up rate and enterprise size of the larger correlation, nearly 90% of micro-and start-up complete shutdown. More than 40 percent of the respondents think the impact of the epidemic is very serious, related to the survival of enterprises. Thirty percent said it would lead to a business that would struggle to survive and not recover for a long time.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Image: Capital Culture think tank

In the eyes of Chen Yitao, in China, Film and Television Company Entrepreneurship is simply the hell model. With the exception of the top 1 percent of the companies, which are largely migrant workers, the production companies have the thinnest margins of all but carry the biggest risks.

However, he is confident that he can pull through this time. He calculated that he would lose 8.5 million yuan for 15 days of downtime, including travel expenses for the crew, living expenses such as lodging and meals for the staff stranded at Hengdian, and the cost of setting up an additional group B. Fortunately, things are looking up. "All Party B, including Hengdian Film and Television Group, gave us a waiver of expenses during the epidemic, and the producer Youku also inquired about our estimated losses and made an interim payment in advance. We share a little, and the damage is manageable."

Chen estimates that the current loss is within a million, "the show will still make a profit, just a little less. ". Recently, he bought 6,500 masks on behalf of the production team and donated them to the desperate city of Xinyang in Henan Province.

A bail-out for the film and Television Industry has begun. On February 1, the Hengdian World Studios announced that, in an effort to minimize the loss of the cast and crew, it would offer all of its bases and studios free of charge during the shutdown, and cut the crew's hotel bill in half, in addition, a monthly rent allowance of 300 yuan and a living allowance of 200 yuan will be provided to each member of the actors guild in Hengdian. At the same time, the Beijing Film Association, Guizhou Film Industry Association, Fujian Association of Film Artists and other institutions also issued a statement, called for the property to reduce or waive the rental of cinema premises.

But not everyone is as lucky as Chen. Can Not Start the small and medium-sized film and television companies are the first to face financial pressure. In particular, under the current situation, the platform's payback period is longer and longer, the producer's advance capital pressure is increasing.

In Liu Lei's view, many film and television companies are already strapped for cash. The ones that can start up now are already qualified companies. Once they stop filming midway for a month or two, if they are put in the industry with sufficient funds, they may still be able to survive, but under the current circumstances, we're facing an existential crisis. "It's better to do custom shows for the platform. It's still difficult to do pure copyrighted shows without the support of the owners. It's possible that head companies will also be affected. "

The famine may hit in the third and fourth quarters of this year. "Most of the dramas that started up a while ago are headliners. The video platforms can be adjusted because they are broadcast online, but many TV stations have reserved their schedules for them. The current situation will test the ability of the TV stations to schedule broadcasts, " Liu said. However, in her view, the outbreak is also good for the drama industry, especially for companies such as Huace and Huanrui Century, which have high inventories.

However, in the view of Ma Zhongjun, the backlog of drama to usher in the dividend period of the argument is not strong, "the project is not sold or sold. ". "TV stations, video platforms, they still have to have quality shows, so they have ratings, traffic and advertising. Theoretically, it will bring about a severe shortage, but a satellite TV is so five, this year the broadcast of the project in general last year will have reserves and planning. The three video platforms have a lot of home-made projects and are still hungry for first-line projects."

Ma Zhongjun revealed that the impact of the ban is continuing, as long as the policy does not open up, part of the costume drama will still be affected. At present, CIWEN media has no backlog of upcoming dramas.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"Youthfulness 2" has been suspended due to an epidemic

Also hit by the outbreak are variety shows. According to a study by CITIC Securities Media, from the first day of the Lunar New Year to the sixth day of the Lunar New Year in 2020, the effective broadcast volume of variety shows dropped by 29.62% , mainly due to the suspension of TV variety shows such as Happy Camp and The Negotiator under the influence of the epidemic.

Liu Lei believes that the biggest impact in the variety field is in fact market confidence. Variety's business model is to find the name sponsor first. On the one hand, the TV station and the video platform have signed a contract with the advertiser in the early stage, and the money has been paid. Under the impact of the epidemic, this amount needs to be recalculated with the advertiser, in the longer term, the outbreak could affect market confidence in the future. "The epidemic has had a huge impact on real businesses like consumer electronics and autos, and when their own cash flow is affected, they may cut back on some of their advertising budgets, " he said

The outbreak of the cold winter in the film and Television Industry, Ma Zhongjun hope the government can be aimed at the film and television industry to introduce some good policies. On the one hand, he wants to limit the subject matter so as to increase the industry's tolerance and activity. On the other hand, in his view, many enterprises do not receive accounts receivable is already a big problem in the industry, the introduction of the film and Television Industry for the poor policy will be conducive to the healthy development of the industry.

###Bad Times and good opportunities

In the face of a possible dramatic shortage, Chen hopes that the state will introduce relevant policies to encourage film and television companies to set up projects. He also does not agree with the current industry "to inventory" argument, in his view, most of the inventory is not sold drama. "It's not just bad for the industry to keep bad companies alive, " he said. "capital has created a huge influx of untrained people into every aspect of film and television production, and the industry is already overproducing. "

Film and Television in the winter, the epidemic of the film and Television Company's crisis... all kinds of difficulties also let the industry in the past the accumulated disadvantages have emerged.

Chen Yitao experienced the film and television industry from the people more money to depression bleak cycle. Before the establishment of Huachen Meichuang, he did IP business, sold "Yun Xi Zhuan" , "Demon Master Kiss me" and other explosive Ip, when the film and television industry into the cold winter, he suddenly found that selling Ip does not make money. Before the business is difficult to do, he took out a reserve of high-quality Ip for adaptation, the formation of their own shooting company. In more than two years, he cut from the lower cost of the sweet pet drama, with the sale of Ip accumulated under the project and market judgment, "why boss to marry me" , "one night bride" two projects can be classified as sub-areas of explosive money.

"In the past, there was too much hot money and people were chasing too high profit margins, which hurt the industry. Some of the shows that cost two million per episode sold ten million per episode, which is not normal, and these companies would be in trouble if one of their shows got stuck, but in Chen's view, the current 50 million film bottom line is still too high, film and television production other links to earn less than a fraction of the actor's salary.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photograph: Jon's Mom

But in the midst of the crisis there is no shortage of opportunities brought about by the New Forces of film and Television. The collective withdrawal of Chinese New Year films has given birth to the collaboration between Mama Jiong and bytedance, and has provided a turning point for the development of online theaters dominated by video platforms. Since then, Donnie Yen's new theatrical release, the Fat Dragon Crossing, has also premiered on Iqiyi and tencent, in contrast to the free version of lost mom, which aims to promote the pay per view model for movies.

Is it possible that the epidemic-driven movie-lead-point-view model will become the norm in China? According to Ma, the controversy over the online premiere of lost mom started in Hollywood a few years ago, but he believes that new media broadcasting is a trend and that in the future quite a number of films can choose to have their online premieres, thus and the cinema line projection forms "two legs" the walking situation.

"It's a fluke that bytedance is using 'lost mom' to draw attention to its long-distance video business, but the pay-per-view of 'the way of the Dragon' could represent the future. Netflix pioneered the charging model for online platforms, and it's only a matter of time before domestic video sites catch on."

In addition to waist movies like "the way of the Fat Dragon, " Ma feels that head movies can also be screened on the Internet. In the future, going to the cinema may be more about seeing films with strong visual and auditory impact. Films that are suitable for families such as "Lost in translation" can be seen both on the cinema line and online, and will not be greatly affected, and with the popularity of 5G, video is smoother, the bigger the screen, the better the audio-visual effect. "The main channel for netflix's 'the Irishman' is the Internet. Director, actor's weight these are not the decisive factor actually, if the click quantity does not lose the theater line, the movie why can not broadcast in the network theater line? Now it's all about ratings."

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo: CITIC Securities Media Research

Staying at home also gives people more leisure time to spend on video sites. According to the CITIC Securities Media Research, from the whole platform situation, 2020 January to the sixth day, the effective broadcast volume of the series rose 11.71% . IQIYI and mango TV are up 36% and 101% respectively, with iqiyi breaking 400 million, tencent video breaking 200 million, and watermelon video hitting 43 million with lost mom.

And as the upstream content production has not been large-scale resumption of work, the next period of time for the major platforms for the content of copyright will intensify the fight. At the BBC Showcase 2020 recently, BBC Studios announced a content deal with Youku that will see a number of critically acclaimed shows launched on Youku over the next few months. The deal includes an extension of the Sherlock's four season license and a total of more than 80 hours of television content, including good omen, Sanditon and the latest season of doctor who.

In a sudden outbreak of the epidemic, the industry pattern will change subtly, but more ordinary practitioners can only wait for the industry to warm up. Zhao Xun, a screenwriter who wrote the online drama the best of us, told the audience: What will happen to the cinema, what will happen to the backlog of films, what will happen to the funding chain, what will happen to the schedule of follow up projects, and what will happen to the personnel, this is certainly something that many people have predicted, but these judgments are now based on logic, and as long as the inflection point doesn't come, no one will be able to give a definitive answer.

"Then do your homework and wait, " Zhao Xun said.
